		"name": "Employee Management API",
		"description": "## üì¶ Employee Management API ‚Äî Postman Collection\n\nThis Postman collection provides a comprehensive set of API requests for interacting with the **Employee Management System**, built using **FastAPI** and secured with **JWT-based authentication**.\n\n### üîê Authentication\n\n- Implements **token-based authentication (JWT)**\n    \n- Access tokens are automatically generated via the login endpoint\n    \n- Tokens are stored in the Postman environment and reused across requests\n    \n\n### üßë‚Äçüíº Role-Based Access Control\n\n- **Admin users** have full access to create, update, and delete employees\n    \n- **Regular users** have read-only access to employee data\n    \n- Authorization is enforced server-side and validated on every request\n    \n\n### üìã Employee Management Features\n\n- Create, retrieve, update, and delete employees\n    \n- Pagination support for large datasets\n    \n- Filtering by department and role\n    \n- Duplicate email validation to ensure data integrity\n    \n\n### üß™ Testing & Validation\n\n- Designed for easy testing and exploration of API behavior\n    \n- Includes clear request bodies and example responses\n    \n- Supports real-world workflows such as login ‚Üí token reuse ‚Üí CRUD operations\n    \n\n### üõ† Environment Configuration\n\nThe collection uses environment variables for flexibility:\n\n- `{{base_url}}` ‚Äî API base URL\n    \n- `{{token}}` ‚Äî JWT access token (auto-updated after login)\n    \n\nThis collection is suitable for:\n\n- Local development\n    \n- API testing and debugging\n    \n- Technical assessments and demos\n    \n- Backend integration with frontend applications",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
